    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "@SergeyOrshanskiy It&#39;s useful for when, depending on how you construct an object, you need to create an anonymous class that implements an interface in order to instantiate a member variable, but you don&#39;t want it to be used. If you set it to <code>null</code> and you accidentally used it (or someone else did) you would get <code>NullPointerExceptions</code> which are less obvious than <code>UnsupportedOperationExceptions</code> in this case. Just an example."
  } ],
