      "comment_id" : 95993512,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Be aware this is an <i>unchecked</i> <code>RuntimeException</code>.  You will get no feedback or assistance in handling these exceptions during compile time.  If this is used for a stubbed method or a work-in-progress you should use some kind of <i>checked</i> exception."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 2996624,
        "reputation" : 818,
        "user_id" : 2543055,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 83,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Hrslq.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Simeon",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2543055/simeon"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 3,
      "creation_date" : 1656503913,
      "post_id" : 829139,
      "comment_id" : 128588005,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "You might wanna do it like this to indicate, that the implementation is yet to come:      throw new java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException(&quot;Not implemented yet.&quot;); //todo implement"
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 952426,
        "reputation" : 2112,
        "user_id" : 978302,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 60,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Qsps3.png?s=256",
        "display_name" : "RenatoIvancic",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/978302/renatoivancic"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1668954506,
      "post_id" : 829139,
      "comment_id" : 131526393,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "It can be puzzling to find public API methods that don&#39;t implement logic yet and return <code>null</code> value. I prefer having a method returning <code>UnsupportedOperationException</code>. I use this myself and rewrite any existing code with this exception, when obviously no logic was implemented."
    } ],
