    "question_id" : 829136,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Differentiate between the two cases you named:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>To indicate that the requested operation is not supported and most likely never will, throw an <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/UnsupportedOperationException.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>UnsupportedOperationException</code></a>.</p></li>\n<li><p>To indicate the requested operation has not been implemented yet, choose between this:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>Use the <a href=\"http://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/javadocs/api-release/org/apache/commons/lang3/NotImplementedException.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>NotImplementedException</code></a> from <a href=\"http://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">apache commons-lang</a> which was available in commons-lang2 and has been re-added to commons-lang3 in version 3.2.</p></li>\n<li><p>Implement your own <code>NotImplementedException</code>.</p></li>\n<li><p>Throw an <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/UnsupportedOperationException.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>UnsupportedOperationException</code></a> with a message like \"Not implemented, yet\".</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 203782,
      "reputation" : 55355,
      "user_id" : 451634,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 58,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/360ebfce7ad37f53a1302f8e68843139?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Benny Neugebauer",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/451634/benny-neugebauer"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 43,
    "last_activity_date" : 1486981970,
    "creation_date" : 1486981970,
    "answer_id" : 42201906,
    "question_id" : 829136,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you create a new (not yet implemented) function in <a href=\"https://netbeans.org/\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><strong>NetBeans</strong></a>, then it generates a method body with the following statement:</p>\n\n<pre><code>throw new java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException(\"Not supported yet.\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Therefore, I recommend to use the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/?java/lang/UnsupportedOperationException.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">UnsupportedOperationException</a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3130088,
      "reputation" : 46062,
      "user_id" : 2648077,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 80,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a465e5bf1c71410211094e09a44d574a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Alireza Fattahi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2648077/alireza-fattahi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 7,
    "last_activity_date" : 1636436588,
    "creation_date" : 1636436588,
    "answer_id" : 69893319,
    "question_id" : 829136,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The below <code>Calculator</code> sample class shows the difference</p>\n<pre><code>public class Calculator() {\n\n int add(int a , int b){\n    return a+b;\n  }\n\n  int dived(int a , int b){\n        if ( b == 0 ) {\n           throw new UnsupportedOperationException(&quot;I can not dived by zero, \n                         not now not for the rest of my life!&quot;)\n        }else{\n          return a/b;\n       }\n   }\n\n   int multiple(int a , int b){\n      //NotImplementedException from apache or some custom excpetion\n      throw new NotImplementedException(&quot;Will be implement in release 3.5&quot;);\n   } \n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
